ball team|Serbia U17]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 19\n| nationalgoals2 = 16\n| nationalyears3 = 2015\n| nationalteam3 = [[Serbia national under-18 football team|Serbia U18]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 1\n| nationalgoals3 = 1\n| nationalyears4 = 2014\u20132016\n| nationalteam4 = [[Serbia national under-19 football team|Serbia U19]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 13\n| nationalgoals4 = 10\n| nationalyears5 = 2016\n| nationalteam5 = [[Serbia national under-20 football team|Serbia U20]]\n| nationalcaps5 = 1\n| nationalgoals5 = 0\n| nationalyears6 = 2015\u20132019\n| nationalteam6 = [[Serbia national under-21 football team|Serbia U21]]\n| nationalcaps6 = 16\n| nationalgoals6 = 7\n| nationalyears7 = 2018\u20132019\n| nationalteam7 = [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]]\n| nationalcaps7 = 7\n| nationalgoals7 = 2\n| club-update = 16:52, 9 February 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 7 September 2019\n}}\n'''Luka Jovi\u0107''' ({{lang-sr-Cyrl|\u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430 \u0408\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b}}, {{IPA-sh|l\u00fb\u02d0ka j\u01d2\u02d0\u028bit\u0255|pron}}; born 23 December 1997) is a Serbian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Spanish club [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] and the [[Serbia national football team|Serbia national team]] as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]].\n\n==Early life==\nJovi\u0107 was born in the small village of Batar near [[Bijeljina]], to Milan and Svetlana Jovi\u0107. At the age of five, he started playing football in [[Loznica]], where he was spotted in 2004 and offered to play in Mini Maxi, a development league for kids aged between 4 and 12 in [[Belgrade]]. After just one game where Jovi\u0107 scored three goals his father was offered \u20ac50 for each game he played and 2,000 [[Bosnia and Herzegovina dinar|dinars]] for travelling costs from Batar to Belgrade. At one of those games he was scouted by Toma Mili\u0107evi\u0107, [[Red Star Belgrade|Red Star's]] scout who invited him to trial with Red Star Belgrade.<ref name=\"Cudo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mozzartsport.com/vesti/cudesan-slucaj-luke-jovica-ili-kako-je-klinac-koji-je-spavao-u-gepeku-stigao-do-velike-pozornice/67871|title=Mozzart Sport: ''\u010cudesan slu\u010daj Luke Jovi\u0107a, ili \u2013 Kako je klinac koji je spavao u gepeku stigao do velike pozornice''|language=Serbian|date=27 December 2013}}</ref> His playing style attracted comparisons to [[Darko Pan\u010dev]] and [[Radamel Falcao]], who is also his idol.<ref name=\"TerzaJovic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sportske.net/vest/domaci-fudbal/terzic-luka-jovic-novi-falkao-190342.html|author=OBRENOVI\u0106, Aleksandar|title=Terzi\u0107: Luka Jovi\u0107 je novi Falkao|date=11 August 2014|access-date=12 May 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605065259/https://www.sportske.net/vest/domaci-fudbal/terzic-luka-jovic-novi-falkao-190342.html|archive-date=5 June 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Novosti\">{{cite web|url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/sport.294.html:459005-Zvezdin-biser-Jovic-Hocu-kao-Pancev|author=B. Cvetojevic|title=Zvezdin biser Jovi\u0107: Ho\u0107u kao Pan\u010dev|date=16 October 2013|language=Serbian}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===Red Star Belgrade===\n====Youth====\nJovi\u0107 was offered the chance to play for [[Red Star Belgrade]] in 2005. Before he committed, his father took him to train with [[FK Partizan|Partizan]], who had been trying to sign Jovi\u0107 for some time. They offered his father \u20ac200 per month for Jovi\u0107 to play with them, but he insisted on staying with Red Star.<ref name=\"Cudo\" />\n\n====2013\u201314 season====\nOn 28 May 2014, at the age of 16 years, five months and five days, Jovi\u0107 made his professional debut against [[FK Vojvodina]] in [[Novi Sad]], where he broke [[Dejan Stankovi\u0107]]'s record as the youngest goalscorer in a competitive match in the club's history.<ref name=\"Blic\">{{cite web|url=http://sport.blic.rs/Fudbal/Domaci-fudbal/253382/Zvezda-je-rodjena-Luka-Jovic-srusio-rekord-Dekija-Stankovica-VIDEO|author=Todorovi\u0107, N.|title=Zvezda je ro\u0111ena: Luka Jovi\u0107 sru\u0161io rekord Dekija Stankovi\u0107a|language=Serbian|date=28 May 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140722085218/http://sport.blic.rs/Fudbal/Domaci-fudbal/253382/Zvezda-je-rodjena-Luka-Jovic-srusio-rekord-Dekija-Stankovica-VIDEO|archivedate=22 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mondo.rs/a696618/Sport/Fudbal/Luka-Jovic-nece-otici-dok-ne-napuni-18.html|title=Luka Jovi\u0107 ne\u0107e oti\u0107i dok ne napuni 18|work=Mondo Portal|accessdate=20 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810115536/http://mondo.rs/a696618/Sport/Fudbal/Luka-Jovic-nece-otici-dok-ne-napuni-18.html|archive-date=10 August 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> He scored the goal only two minutes<ref name=\"Blic\" /> after he was brought on as substitute, and the final score of 3\u20133 was enough to give Red Star the 2013\u201314 [[Serbian SuperLiga]] title.\n\n====2014\u201315 season====\nOn 18 October 2014, Jovi\u0107 became the youngest player ever to play in [[Eternal derby (Serbia)|Eternal derby]] at the age of 16 years, 9 months and 25 days, breaking the previous record of [[Dejan Milovanovi\u0107]] who was 17 years and 6 months old at the time.<ref>[http://www.mozzartsport.com/vesti/luka-jovic-najmladji-akter-u-istoriji-vecitih-derbija/87162] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303224245/http://www.mozzartsport.com/vesti/luka-jovic-najmladji-akter-u-istoriji-vecitih-derbija/87162 |date=3 March 2016 }} Mozzart Sport: Luka Jovi\u0107 \u2013 najmla\u0111i akter u istoriji ve\u010ditih derbija! (Serbian) 18 October 2014</ref> Jovi\u0107 missed some crucial chances, but in spring half of the season scored six goals. His first goal of the season came against Vojvodina, in a match where Red Star celebrated its 70th birthday. He then scored against [[FK Spartak Zlatibor Voda|Spartak]], a double against [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac]] and a decisive goal against [[FK Vo\u017edovac|Vo\u017edovac]], ahead of the Eternal derby clash.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mojacrvenazvezda.net/107215/2015/04/18/evrogol-i-nastavak-serije-luke-jovica-za-minimalac-zvezde-na-vracaru-pred-derbi/|title=\u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043e\u043b \u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043a \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0435 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0435 \u0408\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0446 \u0417\u0432\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0412\u0440\u0430\u0447\u0430\u0440\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434 \u0434\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0438!|author=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440|date=18 April 2015|work=Moja Crvena Zvezda|accessdate=20 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604172217/http://www.mojacrvenazvezda.net/107215/2015/04/18/evrogol-i-nastavak-serije-luke-jovica-za-minimalac-zvezde-na-vracaru-pred-derbi/|archive-date=4 June 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> He missed the end of the season and the [[2015 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in [[New Zealand]] due to injury. On 17 May 2015, he signed a three-year contract with Red Star to last until 2018.\n\n====2015\u201316 season====\nFrom the beginning of the 2015\u201316 season, Jovi\u0107 started as a first choice in Red Star attack along with [[Hugo Filipe Oliveira|Hugo Vieira]] and scored 3 goals in first 5 games. He scored again against Vo\u017edovac a winning goal and brought another win to Red Star at [[Obili\u0107 Stadium|Stadion na Vra\u010daru]]. He scored another game winner in Subotica, against Spartak. In November 2015, a [[racketeer]] from Loznica threatened him and his family that if they did not pay money to him, that he would \"break Jovi\u0107's legs\".<ref name=\"Blicrek\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blic.rs/vesti/hronika/reketas-pretio-da-ce-luki-jovicu-da-polomi-noge/d9cq2rz|author=Miljan Milo\u0161evi\u0107|title=Reketa\u0161 pretio da \u0107e Luki Jovi\u0107u da polomi noge|language=Serbian|date=16 November 2015|accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref> A suspect was apprehended immediately afterwards.<ref name=\"Blicrek\" />\n\n===Benfica===\nIn February 2016, Jovi\u0107 signed with Portuguese champions [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] until 2021.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223213443/http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/44570/language/pt-PT/.aspx |title=Jovi\u0107: \"Aprender e melhorar todos os dias\" |language=Portuguese |trans-title=Jovi\u0107: \"To learn and improve everyday\" |date=2 February 2016 |publisher=S.L. Benfica |access-date=2 February 2016}}</ref> On 9 March, he debuted for the club's [[S.L. Benfica|reserve team]] in a 2\u20132 home draw against [[S.C. Covilh\u00e3|Sporting da Covilh\u00e3]] in the [[Segunda Liga]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ligaportugal.pt/oou/jogo/20152016/ledmanligapro/34/9|title=SL Benfica B \u2013 SC Covilh\u00e3 (Jornada 34 Ledman LigaPRO 2015\u20132016) \u2013 Liga Portugal|work=ligaportugal.pt|accessdate=20 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409215219/http://www.ligaportugal.pt/oou/jogo/20152016/ledmanligapro/34/9|archive-date=9 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He debuted for the first-team on 20 March, as a substitute, in a 1\u20130 away victory against [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] in the [[2015\u201316 Primeira Liga|Primeira Liga]].\n\nOn 30 January 2017, Jovi\u0107 made his only appearance for the first team when he came on as a substitute in the 81st minute against [[Vit\u00f3ria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Set\u00fabal]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1104173/Live/Portugal-Liga-NOS-2016-2017-Vitoria-de-Setubal-Benfica | title = Match Report | publisher = whoscored.com | accessdate = 16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Loan to Eintracht Frankfurt===\n====2017\u201318 season====\nIn June 2017, Jovi\u0107 joined [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on a two-season loan while his new club secured an option to sign him on a permanent basis.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fix: Eintracht leiht Jovic von Benfica aus|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/700477/artikel_fix_eintracht-leiht-jovic-von-benfica-aus.html|accessdate=27 June 2017|work=kicker Online|date=27 June 2017|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=27 June 2017|title=Luka Jovic no Eintracht Frankfurt|trans-title=Luka Jovic at Eintracht Frankfurt|url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/30/news/info/Nan6iq1DhUCZJ-LoPcyJbg|language=Portuguese|website=S.L. Benfica|access-date=4 July 2017}}</ref> He made five appearances as they won the [[2017\u201318 DFB-Pokal]], and scored the only goal of the win at [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] in the semi-finals on 18 April 2018,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Da Silva |first1=Michael |last2=Harding |first2=Jonathan |title=German Cup: Niko Kovac guides Frankfurt to Berlin for Bayern Munich showdown |url=https://www.dw.com/en/german-cup-niko-kovac-guides-frankfurt-to-berlin-for-bayern-munich-showdown/a-43445046 |accessdate=21 October 2018 |publisher=Deutsche Welle |date=18 April 2018}}</ref> but was an unused substitute in the [[2018 DFB-Pokal Final|3\u20131 final win]] over [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].\n\n====2018\u201319 season====\n20-year-old Jovi\u0107 became the youngest player to score five goals in a Bundesliga game when he did so in a 7\u20131 home win over [[Fortuna D\u00fcsseldorf]] on 19 October 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Eintracht Frankfurt 7\u20131 Fortuna Dusseldorf |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45922808 |accessdate=21 October 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=19 October 2018}}</ref> On 14 March 2019, he scored the only goal, his seventh for the campaign, in a 1\u20130 win over [[Inter Milan]] to secure the club's progression to the quarter finals of the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]. In doing so, he helped Eintracht become the first German club ever to record eight wins in a single season in the competition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/inter-milan-eintracht-frankfurt-live-europa-league-line-ups-stats-icardi-jovic-2969|title=Eintracht Frankfurt through to UEFA Europa League quarter-finals after Luka Jovic chip downs Inter Milan|publisher=Bundesliga|date=14 March 2019|accessdate=15 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605232225/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/inter-milan-eintracht-frankfurt-live-europa-league-line-ups-stats-icardi-jovic-2969|archive-date=5 June 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 April 2019, Eintracht Frankfurt exercised a clause in Jovi\u0107's contract to make his loan move permanent until 30 June 2023.<ref>{{cite news|date=17 April 2019|title=Eintracht Frankfurt exercise option to purchase Luka Jovi\u0107|url=https://www.eintracht.de/en/news/article/eintracht-frankfurt-exercise-option-to-purchase-luka-jovic-72250/|work=Eintracht Frankfurt|access-date=18 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418222346/https://www.eintracht.de/en/news/article/eintracht-frankfurt-exercise-option-to-purchase-luka-jovic-72250/|archive-date=18 April 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Real Madrid===\nOn 4 June 2019, Jovi\u0107 signed for [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] for a reported \u20ac60&nbsp;million, on a six-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/06/official-announcement-jovi%C4%87|title=Official Announcement: Jovi\u0107|date=4 June 2019|publisher=Real Madrid C.F.|access-date=4 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/realmadrid/luka-jovic-real-madrid-transfer-confirmed-eintracht-frankfurt-striker-a4145291.html|title=Luka Jovic to Real Madrid transfer confirmed for Eintracht Frankfurt striker|last=Ouzia|first=Malik|date=4 June 2019|work=London Evening Standard|access-date=4 June 2019}}</ref> He made his debut on 17 August 2019, coming in as a substitute in a 3\u20131 win over [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/cronica/2019/08/17/5d5833a022601df81e8b4584.html|title=Real Madrid of old resurrected in Balaidos|date=17 August 2019|work=marca.com|access-date=17 August 2019}}</ref> On 30 October 2019, he scored his first goal for the club in a 5\u20130 victory over [[CD Legan\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Real Madrid vs. Leganes \u2013 Football Match Summary \u2013 October 30, 2019 \u2013 ESPN |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=550508 |website=ESPN |accessdate=30 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nJovi\u0107 started both semi-final and [[2019\u201320 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a Final|final]] match of [[2019\u201320 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]] against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] and [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]], respectively. Real won the final 4\u20131 on [[Penalty shootout|penalties]] on 12 January 2020, earning Jovi\u0107 his first trophy as a Real Madrid player.\n\n==International career==\nOn 11 December 2013, Jovi\u0107 scored a [[hat-trick]] for [[Serbia national under-17 football team|Serbia U-17]] in a 4\u20131 win against [[Croatia national under-17 football team|Croatia U-17]].<ref name=\"Mozzart1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mozzartsport.com/vesti/luka-jovic-terorisao-hrvate-u-pazovi/66885|title=Luka Jovi\u0107 terorisao Hrvate u Pazovi!|language=Serbian|date=11 December 2013}}</ref> In July 2014, he was called up by youth coach [[Veljko Paunovi\u0107]] to [[Serbia national under-19 football team|Serbia's U-19]] [[2014 UEFA European Under-19 Championship squads#Serbia|squad]] for the [[2014 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]].<ref>[http://novosti.rs/vesti/sport.294.html:499882-Na-Paunovicevom-spisku-po-cetiri-igraca-Zvezde-Vojvodine-i-OFK-Beograda-tri-Partizana] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809132743/http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/sport.294.html:499882-Na-Paunovicevom-spisku-po-cetiri-igraca-Zvezde-Vojvodine-i-OFK-Beograda-tri-Partizana |date=9 August 2019 }} Novosti: Na Paunovi\u0107evom spisku po \u010detiri igra\u010da Zvezde, Vojvodine i OFK Beograda, tri Partizana... (Serbian) 8 July 2014</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, Jovi\u0107 was named in [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]]'s preliminary squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.fss.rs/index.php?id=2021&aid=13898 |title=\u0408\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d \u0442\u0438\u043c, \u0441\u0440\u0446\u0435\u043c \u0441\u0432\u0438\u043c \u2013 \u041c\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d \u041a\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0458\u0438\u045b \u043e\u0434\u0430\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043e |trans-title=One team, with all their hearts \u2013 Mladen Krstaji\u0107 selects |website=FSS.rs |publisher=[[Football Association of Serbia]] |date=24 May 2018 |access-date=24 May 2018 |language=Serbian}}</ref> On 4 June, he made his international debut in a friendly match against [[Chile national football team|Chile]], coming on as a substitute for [[Aleksandar Mitrovi\u0107 (footballer)|Aleksandar Mitrovi\u0107]] in the 84th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/06/04/world/friendlies/serbia/chile/2786472/|title=Serbia vs. Chile \u2013 4 June 2018}}</ref> Later in June, Jovi\u0107 was included in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#Serbia|final 23-man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-soccer-worldcup-srb-squad/soccer-krstajic-names-serbias-final-23-man-world-cup-squad-idUSKCN1IX5O2 | title=Soccer: Krstajic names Serbia's final 23-man World Cup squad | agency=Reuters | date=1 June 2018 | accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref> where he appeared as a late substitute against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/27/sports/world-cup/brazil-vs-serbia.html|title=World Cup: Brazil cruises into next round with easy victory|newspaper=The New York Times|author=Andrew Das|date=27 June 2018|accessdate=27 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March 2019, Jovi\u0107 scored his debut goal for the national team in a friendly against [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47644286 |title =Germany 1 Serbia 1|date=20 March 2019|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=28 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWhen Jovi\u0107 was 10 years old, his older sister survived [[leukemia]]. He stated that period had \"left a mark on their lives\" and had motivated him to become a \"fighter like her\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.blic.rs/zabava/luka-jovic-zivotna-prica-sestra-leukemija/5sbrljq|title=\"TO MI JE OBELE\u017dILO \u017dIVOT\" Sestra Luke Jovi\u0107a je pobedila LEUKEMIJU, potresna pri\u010da kida du\u0161u, a kad \u010dujete njegovu poruku APLAUDIRA\u0106ETE MU|accessdate=11 February 2020|date=3 December 2019|author=J. K.|publisher=[[Blic]]|lang=sr}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February 2019, Jovi\u0107 became a father of a baby boy, David, following a fling with his former girlfriend An\u0111ela Manita\u0161evi\u0107, whom he split up with in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.kurir.rs/sport/fudbal/3210683/mladi-napadac-postao-otac-luka-jovic-dobio-sina|title=MLADI NAPADA\u010c POSTAO OTAC: Luka Jovi\u0107 dobio sina!|publisher=[[Kurir]]|author=M. B.|date=24 February 2019|accessdate=11 February 2020|lang=sr}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.blic.rs/zabava/andjela-manitasevic-o-vezi-luke-jovica-i-sofije-milosevic/jvcxqz1|title=\"ZATRUDNELA SAM NEPLANIRANO, NISMO ZAJEDNO TRI GODINE\" Devojka sa kojom Luka Jovi\u0107 ima sina progovorila, ima poruku za njega i Sofiju Milo\u0161evi\u0107|publisher=[[Blic]]|author=J. K.|date=24 October 2019|accessdate=11 February 2020|lang=sr}}</ref> As of summer 2019, he is in a relationship with Serbian model [[Sofija Milo\u0161evi\u0107]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://dnevnik.hr/showbuzz/celebrity/luka-jovic-i-sofija-milosevic-potvrdili-vezu---586801.html|title=Prvo je demantirao glasine o vezi s njom, no sad je priznao da ljubi jednu od najljep\u0161ih Srpkinja|publisher=Dnevnik.hr|author=E. D.|accessdate=11 February 2020|date=13 December 2019|lang=hr}}</ref> On 20 March 2020, Milo\u0161evi\u0107 announced that she and Jovi\u0107 are expecting their first child.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.kurir.rs/sport/fudbal/3431547/luka-jovic-postaje-tata-po-drugi-put-sofija-milosevic-trduna-manekenka-podelila-srecne-vesti-na-drustvenim-mrezama|title=LUKA JOVI\u0106 POSTAJE TATA PO DRUGI PUT! SOFIJA MILO\u0160EVI\u0106 TRUDNA! Manekenka podelila sre\u0107ne vesti na dru\u0161tvenim mre\u017eama|date=20 March 2020|work=[[Kurir]]|access-date=|url-status=live|language=Serbian}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March 2020, amid the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe]], Jovi\u0107 broke Serbia's self-isolation protocol by flying from [[Madrid]] to Belgrade to attend Milo\u0161evi\u0107's birthday party, drawing criticism from [[Prime Minister of Serbia]] [[Ana Brnabi\u0107]] herself and facing possible [[Criminal charge|charges]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/real-madrid/story/4076402/real-madrids-jovic-facing-criticism-in-serbia-after-travelling-home-amid-team-lockdown|title=Real Madrid's Jovic facing criticism in Serbia after travelling home amid team lockdown for coronavirus|last=Kirkland|first=Alex|date=19 March 2020|website=[[ESPN]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 26 February 2020}}<ref>{{ForaDeJogo|accessdate=3 January 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{Soccerway|accessdate=15 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n! colspan=\"2\"|League\n! colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n! colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n! colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n! colspan=\"2\"|Other<sup>1</sup>\n! colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Red Star Belgrade]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Serbian SuperLiga|2013\u201314]]\n|1||1||0||0||cols