{"title_page": "LJ Hooker League", "text_new": "The '''[[LJ Hooker]] League''' is a cricket competition on the [[Northern Rivers|NSW Far North Coast]] comprising teams from the [[Ballina, New South Wales|Ballina]], [[Casino, New South Wales|Casino]] and [[Tweed Heads, New South Wales|Tweed]] District Cricket Associations.\n\nThe League was established in 1994/95 and superseded the top-grade of the Ballina, Casino and [[Lismore, New South Wales|Lismore]] District Competitions.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Attewell |first1=Paul |title=20 years of Far North Coast LJ Hooker League |url=https://www.northernstar.com.au/news/pick-of-the-first-20-years/2571463/ |website=[[The Northern Star]] |accessdate=25 March 2019 |language=en |date=12 March 2005}}</ref> \n\nFor 13 seasons this competition worked well, but a division came about in 2007 when the Tweed District Cricket Association asked to join the league to form a larger 16-team competition.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Miller |first1=Adrian |title=Tweed set to join cricket?s Hooker League |url=https://www.northernstar.com.au/news/apn-tweed-set-to-join-crickets-hooker/14244/ |website=[[The Northern Star]] |accessdate=25 March 2019 |language=en |date=29 March 2007}}</ref> The Ballina clubs voted unanimously to join with the Tweed based clubs, but this was rejected by the Lismore-based teams. The original league was dissolved and since 2007/08, the league comprises teams from Ballina, Casino and Tweed districts.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Miller |first1=Adrian |title=THE GREAT DIVIDE |url=https://www.northernstar.com.au/news/apn-the-great/14012/ |website=[[The Northern Star]] |accessdate=25 March 2019 |language=en |date=11 May 2007}}</ref>\n\nThrough the Far North Coast Cricket Council (region) and North Coastal Zone (zone), the LJ Hooker League feeds into [[Country Cricket New South Wales]].\n\n==Premiers==\n*1994/95: Northern Districts<ref>{{cite web |last1=Craig |first1=Mitchell |title=New cricket captains will be keen to make their mark |